Program: Discovery
Title: Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwqn
Last Broadcast Date: 30 September 1996
How depression could be treated through transcranial magnetic stimulation. A greater understanding of how the brain works is helping scientists develop treatments for depression and possibly dementia. Also in the programme, building a tiny computer on a scaffolding of DNA and an anthropologist talks about his 30 years living among the warring people of Papua New Guinea. Show less